issue.title: Add params to votingPage.html template
issue.body: The voting page's script needs to make use of the event id and user email passed as HTTP params to /vote; hence they need to be added to the votingPage.html template.

issue.title: Yelp API call fails if params missing
issue.body: The Yelp API call fails with error code 400 if any of the params (e.g. date) are missing, as we don't require everything to be filled out nor do we set reasonable defaults.

issue.title: POST to /options has incorrect HTTP method
issue.body: When trying to create a new event and POST to /options while running locally, the call does nothing on my machine. The server reports an HTTP request for “OPTIONS /options”, even though the JavaScript seems to be making a correct POST request and the server returns 200 OK. Moreover this seems to only be an issue on my machine.
